Using a code-aware AI to scaffold a Playwright login test, then fixing the guessed selectors:

```javascript
// AI-generated scaffold (selectors are GUESSES - must be replaced with real ones)
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';

test('user can log in with valid credentials', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto('https://example.com/login');
  await page.fill('#email', 'qa.user@example.com');     // guessed id
  await page.fill('#password', 'Secret123!');           // guessed id
  await page.click('button[type="submit"]');
  await expect(page.getByRole('heading', { name: 'Dashboard' })).toBeVisible();
});

// After inspecting the real DOM, the QA replaces guessed selectors with stable ones:
//   page.fill('#email', ...)    ->  page.getByTestId('login-email')
//   page.fill('#password', ...) ->  page.getByTestId('login-password')
// Then runs `npx playwright test` and confirms it passes before committing.
```
